Multi-head attention is defined as:

MultiHead(Q, K, V) = Concat(head_1, ŌĆ”, head_h) ┬Ę W^O,
where each head_i = Attention(Q┬ĘW_i^Q, K┬ĘW_i^K, V┬ĘW_i^V).

Each head applies the attention function to linearly projected queries (Q), keys (K), and values (V) using learned projection matrices W_i^Q, W_i^K, and W_i^V. The h resulting head outputs are concatenated and passed through an output projection W^O to produce the final multi-head output.

Parameter shapes:
- W_i^Q Ōłł R^{d_model ├Ś d_k}
- W_i^K Ōłł R^{d_model ├Ś d_k}
- W_i^V Ōłł R^{d_model ├Ś d_v}
- W^O Ōłł R^{h┬Ęd_v ├Ś d_model}

Model setting used here: h = 8 heads with d_k = d_v = d_model / h = 64. Because each head works in reduced dimensionality, overall compute is roughly comparable to single-head attention operating at full dimensionality.
